     BotifyX Advanced Satellite Signal Monitoring System Using SDR Technology
Abstract
The BotifyX Advanced Satellite Signal Monitoring System is a low-cost Software Defined Radio (SDR) based ground station designed for educational, research, and radio-frequency monitoring applications. The system uses an antenna, Low Noise Amplifier (LNA), RTL-SDR receiver, and Raspberry Pi or laptop to receive and analyze satellite radio signals. A Python-based dashboard provides real-time signal monitoring, spectrum visualization, and data logging capabilities.
Objective
    • Receive radio-frequency signals from satellites. 
    • Monitor signal strength in real time. 
    • Visualize spectrum data. 
    • Log received data for analysis. 
    • Provide a low-cost educational ground station platform. 
